      "writtenOn": "2019-08-03T00:03:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what is the intention of this package and what problem this package is trying to solve? is the intention is to wire all spanner interaction through this package? Is it going to grow proportional with all use cases, e.g. number of different SQL queries we will send? it is hard to reason about the design being implied here without seeing the full picture, i.e. what\u0027s coming next. That\u0027s why top-\u003ebottom CLs are easier to review, e.g. I expected the next CL to be based on the previous one. I don\u0027t see clearly how we will connect the two. \n\nOptions to consider:\n- send CLs top-to-bottom\n- write a short doc that outlines packages and layers of abstraction that you envision",
