      "writtenOn": "2019-08-05T18:48:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I worked on this bit based on what you mentioned in our 1:1 about having more independent CLs that wouldn\u0027t be blocked on each other. We\u0027ll definitely need /some/ sort of writing to Spanner, so even if this gets refactored and reorganized into a different file structure the basic functionality is still there.\n\nThe intention is to wire Spanner interaction through this package; we\u0027ll have BigQuery interaction later too, and as available storage options change and needs develop we might need to swap out one storage backend for another, so pulling it out into a separate package under storage/ was intended to prevent entwining from the get-go. What do you think?\n\n(In the meantime I can put together a structure outline.)",
      "parentUuid": "eafb41ef_61e1690d",
      "revId": "f7901f5816ba144b2eb15c4c7a6cfbb48d1eb6d1",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
