    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f31aaa36_a0920eb4",
        "filename": "results/k8s/storage/spanner/writer.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-08-05T18:48:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why is that not possible with this abstraction? The intention was that it would be, so it\u0027s a question on (im)possibility, not on level of generality.\n\nThe part that\u0027s missing seems to be the early exit, which should be straightforward to add (pass in an invocation ID, read the invocation in the transaction, early exit if finalized), and the part about it all happening in one transaction is /meant/ to be handled by the fact that it\u0027s the same txn being passed in to ReadWriteTransaction. How do you think is this working instead?",
